
[1]exasperate

   EX`ASPERATE, v.t. [L. exaspero, to irritate; ex and aspero, from asper,
   rough, harsh.]

   1. To anger; to irritate to a high degree; to provoke to rage; to
   enrage; to excite anger, or to inflame it to an extreme degree. We say,
   to exasperate a person, or to exasperate the passion of anger or
   resentment.

   2. To aggravate; to embitter; as, to exasperate enmity.

   3. To augment violence; to increase malignity; to exacerbate; as, to
   exasperate pain or a part inflamed.
